  "title": "Country Manager (Sales / BD)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Company:</strong></p><p>Our client is a global engineering solutions provider serving a diverse range of industries worldwide.</p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li><p>A strategic leader with the capability and ambition to develop into a future Managing Director (MD) for the operations</p></li><li><p>Lead sales, business development, and branch operations to drive sustainable growth</p></li><li><p>Develop and implement business strategy and annual budget. Lead from planning to execution</p></li><li><p>Conduct market research, sales analysis and build sales strategies, including of target selection, competitor analysis, proposal planning, etc.</p></li><li><p>Build and strengthen relationships with key clients, including new business development</p></li><li><p>Build networks with industry associations and business partners</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance, risk management, and handle issues/troubleshooting, including internal/external coordination</p></li><li><p>Lead, supervise, recruit, evaluate, develop, and manage local branch staff</p></li><li><p>Support daily sales activities, for examples, client meetings, sales proposal and negotiations</p></li><li><p>Track sales performance, sales pipeline, forecast and budgeting</p></li><li><p>Perform any other duties as assigned by the company</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proven managerial experience with the ability to lead and develop teams effectively</p></li><li><p>Strong background in Sales and Business Development, preferably within a B2B environment</p></li><li><p>Experience in industrial engineering is advantageous, but not mandatory</p></li><li><p>Demonstrated ability to perform PDCA and drive results</p></li><li><p>Capability to lead execution and continuous improvement, including strategy planning and implement</p></li><li><p>Ability to collaborate with local staff and energize the organization</p></li><li><p>Strong awareness of compliance, market trends and risk management</p></li><li><p>Proficient at MS Excel, Word and PowerPoint</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of ASEAN business and connections with key industry clients is a plus point</p></li></ul><p><strong>Compensation:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Working Hours: 9AM - 6PM (Monday to Friday)</p></li><li><p>AWS</p></li><li><p>Variable Bonus</p></li><li><p>Medical Benefits and Group Insurance<a href=\"https://www.jointhire.com.sg/job/3561?utm_source=followup\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a></p></li></ul>",
